. It will be of interest to scholars who study the Literary Studies, religion, and culture of early modern England, to feminist theologians, and to any reader grappling seriously with gender issues in Christian theology and spirituality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aChristian poetry, EnglishyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish poetryyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aFemininity (Philosophy) in literature. 0aFemininityxReligious aspects. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomenxReligious aspects. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780820705194?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780820705194423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780820705194/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK